main event: Multiple witnesses reported observing unidentified flying objects in Oxford County, Maine, on September 9, 1963.
interesting points: The first witness described a bright, bluish-white light hovering and moving erratically in the sky,The second witness reported a bright circular object that appeared to accelerate rapidly out of sight after 30 seconds,One of the witnesses was a credible and reliable individual with no history of mental illness,Several witnesses reported different shapes and sizes of the UFO,An investigation team dispatched by the Air Force found no physical evidence of the sightings.
sighted object: unidentified flying object described as circular, disc-shaped, and brilliant white-blue light
witness description: One witness was a 42-year-old married man, another was a 48-year-old logger, and the credible witness was a retired Brigadier General in the USAF.
